# Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock II

## Difficulty
Medium

## Approach
Use a greedy approach. Traverse the array and add every positive price difference between consecutive days to the total profit. 
Whenever the price increases from one day to the next, that increase can be treated as a profitable transaction.
By summing all positive differences, the algorithm captures the maximum profit obtainable from multiple buy-and-sell transactions.

## Complexity
- **Time Complexity:** O(n)
- **Space Complexity:** O(1)

## Code
```python
class Solution:
    def maxProfit(self, prices):
        profit = 0

        for i in range(1, len(prices)):
            if prices[i] > prices[i - 1]:
                profit += prices[i] - prices[i - 1]

        return profit
```
